  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "A common challenge in designing ML-based thermal comfort predictors is the issue of class imbalance in data.",
    "Almost all of the thermal comfort datasets (Ličina et al., 2018; Liu et al., 2019) are inherently class-imbalanced, i.e., they have more data belonging to \"Prefer No-Change\" than \"Prefer Warmer\" and \"Prefer Cooler\" thermal preference classes.",
    "Researchers have tackled this issue by using weighed loss functions for ML models.",
    "A related challenge is the overall lack of sufficient amount of data (Liu et al., 2019).",
    "Collecting large amounts of data as required by ML models from humans via real-world experiments is expensive and cumbersome."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
